(472, 'Symplocardalis bulbosa', 'Hogweed or Wispbell', 'There are two kinds of Hogweed, the white and the black. The black sort is likewise called Hen-bit; but the white one is here spoken of. It is only manured in gardens, or larger fields, for the profit that is made thereof. They flower somewhat early, and abide a great while; the leaves continue green until Spring, and sometimes abide, except the Winter be very sharp and cold.', 'symplocardalis-bulbosa', 'Symplocardalis bulbosa\r\nHogweed or Wispbell\r\nThere are two kinds of Hogweed, the white and the black. The black sort is likewise called Hen-bit; but the white one is here spoken of. It is only manured in gardens, or larger fields, for the profit that is m', 0, 0, '2018-09-07 12:30:51', 1536342346, 'Hogweed/Wispbell');
